Q: How can i read cyrillic text from VS2019 console A: <p>Worked for me (C code, GCC on Windows 10):</p>
<pre class="lang-c prettyprint-override"><code>#include &lt;stdio.h&gt;
#include &lt;wchar.h&gt;
#include &lt;fcntl.h&gt;
#include &lt;io.h&gt;

int main() {
    // Переключаем поток ввода-вывода в режим Юникода (UTF-16)
    _setmode(_fileno(stdout), _O_U16TEXT);
    _setmode(_fileno(stdin), _O_U16TEXT);

    char name[100];
    wprintf(L&quot;Введите имя: &quot;);
    wscanf(L&quot;%99ls&quot;, name);
    wprintf(L&quot;Привет, %ls!\n&quot;, name);

    return 0;
}
</code></pre>

Q: How to convert from UTC to local time in C? A: <p>Since C23, use <code>time_t timegm(struct tm *timeptr);</code> to perform the UTC <code>struct tm</code> to <code>time_t</code> step.</p>
<p>Be sure to employ checks for errors.  There are various surprising cases when a time function may fail such as discontinuities in <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/a/79502497/2410359"><code>mktime()</code></a> that render its use with out-of-range member values as brittle.</p>
<pre class="lang-c prettyprint-override"><code>time_t time_utc = timegm(tp);
if (time_utc == -1) Handle_Failure();
struct tm *local = localtime(&amp;time_utc);
if (local == NULL) Handle_Failure();
strftime(buf, sizeof buf, &quot;%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S %Z&quot;, local);
</code></pre>
